---

<ApplicationLayout
  title="Decanter Centrifuge Differential Speed Calculator | Dolphin"
  description="Decanter centrifuge differential speed: formula, calculation examples, and how varying speed affects solids output, cake dryness, and scroll torque protection."
  canonicalUrl="https://dolphincentrifuge.com/decanter-centrifuge-differential-speed/"
  heroImage="/images/diagrams/decanter-bowl-scroll-rotation-nb.webp"
  heroImageAlt="Decanter bowl and scroll differential speed diagram showing bowl and auger rotation"
  category="knowledge"
  categoryLabel="Knowledge Base"
  toc={toc}
  relatedApplications={relatedApplications}
  relatedProducts={relatedProducts}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>

  <!-- AI Summary -->
  <div class="not-prose bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-4 mb-6">
    <p class="text-sm text-text-light leading-relaxed italic">Dolphin Centrifuge supplies decanter centrifuges with adjustable differential speed from 1–40 RPM, operating at 2,000–4,000 G-force. Differential speed optimization controls cake dryness, solids throughput, and scroll torque protection across industrial dewatering applications.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 30-Second Summary -->
  <h2 id="summary">30-Second Summary Takeaway</h2>
  <p>In this article, you will learn about the following aspects of differential speed in a <a href="/decanter-centrifuge/">decanter centrifuge</a>:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>The two rotating speeds of a decanter centrifuge</li>
    <li>What differential speed is and how it is created</li>
    <li>The differential speed formula and a live calculator</li>
    <li>How varying differential speed affects cake dryness and solids output</li>
    <li>Benefits of speed variation and automatic scroll control</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- Two Speeds -->
  <h2 id="two-speeds">What Are the Different Speeds of a Decanter Centrifuge?</h2>

  <figure class="my-6">
    <img src="/images/diagrams/decanter-bowl-scroll-rotation-nb.webp" alt="Decanter Bowl Auger Differential Speed diagram showing cross-section of bowl and scroll rotation" width="735" height="299" loading="lazy" class="rounded-lg w-full" />
    <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-500 text-center mt-2">Decanter Bowl and Scroll — Cross-Sectional View showing Bowl and Auger Rotation</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <p>In technical terms, speed refers to the rotational speed or RPM (Rotations Per Minute) of the decanter's two main rotating components — the outer bowl and the internal scroll conveyor.</p>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-6 not-prose">
    <div class="bg-navy/5 rounded-xl p-5 border border-navy/10">
      <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-navy mb-2 font-heading">Bowl Speed</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-light leading-relaxed">The outer bowl rotates continuously, driven by the main motor through pulleys and belts. This rotation creates centrifugal force that sediments solids along the bowl wall. Bowl speed is fixed during operation — typically 2,000–4,000 RPM.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-gold/10 rounded-xl p-5 border border-gold/20">
      <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-navy mb-2 font-heading">Scroll Speed</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-light leading-relaxed">The internal scroll (auger) rotates inside the bowl at a slightly different speed, conveying accumulated solids toward the discharge ports. The scroll speed is always slightly less than the bowl speed — this difference is the differential speed.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Differential Speed -->
  <h2 id="differential-speed">Decanter Differential Speed</h2>
  <p>The differential speed of a decanter centrifuge is the difference between the bowl's rotational speed and the scroll's rotational speed. It directly determines how long solids remain inside the bowl before being discharged — the <strong>residence time</strong>.</p>
  <p>Longer residence time allows more compression under centrifugal force, producing drier solids cake. Shorter residence time increases solids throughput but yields wetter cake.</p>

  <h3 id="mechanism">The Mechanism to Create Differential Speed</h3>
  <p>The decanter bowl connects to the scroll through a planetary gearbox assembly. The gear ratio within the gearbox determines the base differential speed. A separate back-drive motor controls the sun wheel shaft — varying its speed adjusts the differential in real time.</p>

  <figure class="my-6">
    <img src="/images/decanter-centrifuge-differential-speed/Decanter-Centrifuge-Gearbox-and-Torque-Clutch-Assembly-600.webp" alt="Decanter Centrifuge Gearbox and Torque Clutch Assembly showing the gear mechanism that creates differential speed" width="600" height="450" loading="lazy" class="rounded-lg mx-auto block" />
    <figcaption class="text-sm text-gray-500 text-center mt-2">Decanter Centrifuge Gearbox and Torque Clutch Assembly</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <h3 id="adjustment">Adjustment or Variation</h3>
  <p>Differential speed is changed by controlling the rotation speed of the sun wheel shaft extension of the gearbox. The direction and speed of sun wheel rotation directly determines the actual differential speed of the decanter at any point in time.</p>

  <!-- Calculation -->
  <h2 id="calculation">Differential Speed Calculation</h2>
  <p>Three parameters determine differential speed: <strong>Bowl Speed</strong>, <strong>Sun-Wheel Shaft Speed</strong>, and the <strong>Gearbox Ratio</strong>.</p>

  <div class="bg-navy rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 not-prose">
    <p class="text-xs text-white/60 uppercase tracking-widest mb-1 font-mono">Formula</p>
    <p class="font-mono text-gold text-lg font-bold text-center leading-relaxed">
      Differential Speed = (Bowl Speed &minus; Sun Wheel Shaft Speed) &divide; Gearbox Ratio
    </p>
  </div>

  <p>For example, with a Bowl Speed of <strong>3,500 RPM</strong>, a Gearbox Ratio of <strong>200:1</strong>, and a Sun Wheel Shaft Speed of <strong>1,500 RPM</strong>:</p>

  <div class="bg-navy/5 rounded-xl p-5 mb-6 text-center not-prose border border-navy/10">
    <p class="font-mono text-navy text-base">(3,500 &minus; 1,500) &divide; 200 = <span class="text-2xl font-bold text-gold">10 RPM</span></p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1">Differential Speed Result</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Live Calculator -->
  <h2 id="calculator">Live Differential Speed Calculator</h2>
  <p>Enter your decanter parameters below to instantly calculate differential speed. Adjust the sun wheel shaft speed (via back-drive VFD frequency) to see how differential RPM changes.</p>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 shadow-md overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Calculator Header -->
    <div class="bg-navy px-6 py-4 flex items-center gap-3">
      <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gold flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 7h6m0 10v-3m-3 3h.01M9 17h.01M9 11h.01M12 11h.01M15 11h.01M4 5a2 2 0 012-2h12a2 2 0 012 2v14a2 2 0 01-2 2H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V5z" />
      </svg>
      <h3 class="text-white font-bold font-heading text-base">Decanter Differential Speed Calculator</h3>
      <span class="ml-auto text-xs text-gold/70 font-mono">dolphincentrifuge.com</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Inputs -->
    <div class="p-6 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
      <div>
        <label for="calc-bowl-speed" class="block text-xs font-semibold text-navy uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Bowl Speed (RPM)</label>
        <input
          id="calc-bowl-speed"
          type="number"
          value="4000"
          min="500"
          max="6000"
          step="50"
          class="w-full border border-gray-200 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-navy font-mono text-base focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-gold/50 focus:border-gold"
          oninput="calcDiffSpeed()"
        />
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">Typical range: 2,000 – 4,500 RPM</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <label for="calc-gear-ratio" class="block text-xs font-semibold text-navy uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Gearbox Ratio</label>
        <input
          id="calc-gear-ratio"
          type="number"
          value="159"
          min="50"
          max="500"
          step="1"
          class="w-full border border-gray-200 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-navy font-mono text-base focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-gold/50 focus:border-gold"
          oninput="calcDiffSpeed()"
        />
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">Typical range: 80 – 200:1</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <label for="calc-sun-speed" class="block text-xs font-semibold text-navy uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Sun Wheel Shaft Speed (RPM)</label>
        <input
          id="calc-sun-speed"
          type="number"
          value="2460"
          min="0"
          max="5000"
          step="50"
          class="w-full border border-gray-200 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-navy font-mono text-base focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-gold/50 focus:border-gold"
          oninput="calcDiffSpeed()"
        />
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mt-1">Controlled by back-drive VFD</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Result -->
    <div class="mx-6 mb-6 rounded-xl bg-navy/5 border border-navy/10 px-6 py-5 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-4">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wide font-semibold">Calculated Differential Speed</p>
        <p class="font-mono text-gray-500 text-sm mt-1">
          (<span id="calc-display-bowl">4,000</span> &minus; <span id="calc-display-sun">2,460</span>) &divide; <span id="calc-display-ratio">159</span>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <p id="calc-result" class="text-5xl font-bold font-mono text-gold leading-none">10</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-navy font-semibold mt-1 uppercase tracking-wide">RPM</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex-1 text-right">
        <div id="calc-status" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-green-100 text-green-700">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-green-500 inline-block"></span>
          <span>Normal Range</span>
        </div>
        <p id="calc-guidance" class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-1 max-w-[180px] ml-auto">Typical operating range: 1–30 RPM</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 text-center pb-4">© Dolphin Centrifuge — for reference only. Contact our engineers to verify settings for your specific machine.</p>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    function calcDiffSpeed() {
      const bowl = parseFloat(document.getElementById('calc-bowl-speed').value) || 0;
      const ratio = parseFloat(document.getElementById('calc-gear-ratio').value) || 1;
      const sun = parseFloat(document.getElementById('calc-sun-speed').value) || 0;

      const diff = (bowl - sun) / ratio;
      const result = document.getElementById('calc-result');
      const status = document.getElementById('calc-status');
      const guidance = document.getElementById('calc-guidance');
      const displayBowl = document.getElementById('calc-display-bowl');
      const displaySun = document.getElementById('calc-display-sun');
      const displayRatio = document.getElementById('calc-display-ratio');

      displayBowl.textContent = bowl.toLocaleString();
      displaySun.textContent = sun.toLocaleString();
      displayRatio.textContent = ratio.toLocaleString();

      if (isNaN(diff) || ratio === 0) {
        result.textContent = '—';
        return;
      }

      result.textContent = diff < 0 ? diff.toFixed(1) : Math.round(diff * 10) / 10;

      if (diff < 0) {
        status.className = 'inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-red-100 text-red-700';
        status.innerHTML = '<span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-red-500 inline-block"></span><span>Invalid — Check Inputs</span>';
        guidance.textContent = 'Sun wheel speed cannot exceed bowl speed.';
      } else if (diff === 0) {
        status.className = 'inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-700';
        status.innerHTML = '<span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-yellow-500 inline-block"></span><span>Zero — No Conveyance</span>';
        guidance.textContent = 'Differential speed of 0 means no solids movement.';
      } else if (diff <= 5) {
        status.className = 'inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-blue-100 text-blue-700';
        status.innerHTML = '<span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-blue-500 inline-block"></span><span>Very Low — Max Dryness</span>';
        guidance.textContent = 'Very dry cake — monitor for scroll overload.';
      } else if (diff <= 15) {
        status.className = 'inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-green-100 text-green-700';
        status.innerHTML = '<span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-green-500 inline-block"></span><span>Normal Range</span>';
        guidance.textContent = 'Balanced dryness and solids output capacity.';
      } else if (diff <= 30) {
        status.className = 'inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-amber-100 text-amber-700';
        status.innerHTML = '<span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-500 inline-block"></span><span>High — Wetter Cake</span>';
        guidance.textContent = 'Higher throughput, wetter solids. Check if acceptable.';
      } else {
        status.className = 'inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold bg-red-100 text-red-700';
        status.innerHTML = '<span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-red-500 inline-block"></span><span>Very High — Verify Settings</span>';
        guidance.textContent = 'Exceeds typical 1–30 RPM range. Verify gearbox ratio.';
      }
    }
    // Run on page load
    calcDiffSpeed();
  </script>

  <!-- Speed Reference Table -->
  <h2 id="speed-table">Differential Speed Reference Table</h2>
  <p>The table below shows how adjusting the back-drive motor frequency (VFD Hz) changes the differential RPM for a decanter with a <strong>159:1 gearbox ratio</strong> at <strong>4,000 RPM bowl speed</strong>. As back-drive frequency increases, sun wheel speed increases and differential speed decreases — producing drier cake.</p>

  <div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto my-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm">
    <table class="w-full text-sm">
      <thead>
        <tr class="bg-navy text-white">
          <th colspan="5" class="px-4 py-2 text-left font-mono text-xs text-gold/80 font-normal">
            Gearbox Ratio: <strong class="text-gold">159:1</strong> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Bowl Speed: <strong class="text-gold">4,000 RPM</strong> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Sun-Wheel Shaft Speed: Varying (back-drive VFD)
          </th>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-navy/90 text-white text-xs uppercase tracking-wide">
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">BD Freq (Hz)</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-semibold">BD Motor Speed (RPM)</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-semibold">Scroll Speed (RPM)</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-semibold">Bowl Speed (RPM)</th>
          <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-semibold text-gold">Differential RPM ↓</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr class="bg-white border-b border-gray-100">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">0 Hz</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">0</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono">3,975</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">4,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono font-bold text-navy text-base">25 RPM</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-gray-50 border-b border-gray-100">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">15 Hz</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">615</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono">3,979</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">4,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono font-bold text-navy text-base">21 RPM</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white border-b border-gray-100">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">45 Hz</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">1,845</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono">3,986</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">4,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono font-bold text-navy text-base">13 RPM</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-gold/5 border-b border-gold/20">
          <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">60 Hz</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">2,460</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono">3,990</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono text-gray-600">4,000</td>
          <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right font-mono font-bold text-gold text-base">10 RPM</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
      <tfoot>
        <tr>
          <td colspan="5" class="px-4 py-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-right italic">Higher BD frequency → higher sun wheel speed → lower differential RPM → drier cake, lower throughput</td>
        </tr>
      </tfoot>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Effects -->
  <h2 id="effects">Effects of Higher Differential Speed</h2>
  <p>Higher differential speed reduces solids residence time inside the bowl. This creates a direct trade-off between cake dryness and solids throughput capacity:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher Solids Output Capacity</strong> — faster scroll conveyance evacuates solids more quickly</li>
    <li><strong>Lower Torque Load on Scroll</strong> — solids don't accumulate as heavily before discharge</li>
    <li><strong>Wetter Solids Cake</strong> — shorter residence time means less compression and less dewatering</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="text-sm italic text-gray-600">Scroll conveying speed should never exceed what is required for satisfactory separation — over-speeding wastes energy and produces wet, high-cost-to-dispose cake.</p>

  <!-- SVG Performance Chart -->
  <div class="not-prose my-6">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 shadow-sm overflow-hidden bg-white">
      <div class="bg-navy/5 border-b border-gray-100 px-5 py-3 flex items-center justify-between">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-navy font-heading">Scroll Speed vs. Decanter Performance</p>
        <span class="text-xs text-gray-400 font-mono">dolphincentrifuge.com</span>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 520 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-full h-auto" role="img" aria-label="Chart showing inverse relationship between differential speed, cake dryness, and solids output capacity">
          <title>Scroll Speed Effects on Decanter Performance</title>
          <desc>As differential speed increases, cake dryness decreases while solids output capacity increases. The two lines cross at mid-range, representing the optimal operating point.</desc>

          <!-- Background -->
          <rect x="0" y="0" width="520" height="300" fill="#ffffff"/>

          <!-- Grid lines -->
          <line x1="70" y1="40" x2="70" y2="245" stroke="#e5e7eb" stroke-width="1"/>
          <line x1="160" y1="40" x2="160" y2="245" stroke="#e5e7eb" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
          <line x1="250" y1="40" x2="250" y2="245" stroke="#e5e7eb" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
          <line x1="340" y1="40" x2="340" y2="245" stroke="#e5e7eb" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
          <line x1="430" y1="40" x2="430" y2="245" stroke="#e5e7eb" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
          <line x1="470" y1="40" x2="470" y2="245" stroke="#e5e7eb" stroke-width="1"/>

          <line x1="70" y1="245" x2="470" y2="245" stroke="#e5e7eb" stroke-width="1"/>
          <line x1="70" y1="195" x2="470" y2="195" stroke="#e5e7eb" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
          <line x1="70" y1="145" x2="470" y2="145" stroke="#e5e7eb" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
          <line x1="70" y1="95" x2="470" y2="95" stroke="#e5e7eb" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4,3"/>
          <line x1="70" y1="45" x2="470" y2="45" stroke="#e5e7eb" stroke-width="1"/>

          <!-- Axes -->
          <line x1="70" y1="40" x2="70" y2="250" stroke="#1B3A5C" stroke-width="2"/>
